sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor U as User
  participant C as ClientA / ClientB
  participant SSO as SSO Server
  participant M as MongoDB
  participant R as Redis

  Note over C: /login = OAuth-only<br/>/login-oidc = OIDC (openid email)

  U->>C: Click Login
  C->>C: Generate state + PKCE (code_verifier/code_challenge)

  alt OIDC login (/login-oidc)
    C->>C: Generate nonce
    C->>SSO: GET /authorize (scope=openid email, nonce, state, code_challenge, S256)
  else OAuth-only login (/login)
    C->>SSO: GET /authorize (state, code_challenge, S256)
  end

  SSO->>M: Validate client_id + redirect_uri
  SSO->>R: Save req.session.oauth (client_id, redirect_uri, state, scope, nonce, PKCE)
  SSO-->>U: Render login page

  U->>SSO: POST /login (email, password)
  SSO->>M: Verify user + create AuthCode (scope, nonce, PKCE, expiresAt)
  SSO-->>U: 302 redirect_uri?code&state

  U->>C: GET /callback?code&state
  C->>C: Verify state
  C->>SSO: POST /token (grant_type=authorization_code, code, client creds, redirect_uri, deviceId, deviceType, code_verifier)
  SSO->>SSO: Validate client auth + code + PKCE + expiry
  SSO->>R: Create session + deviceSession + userSessions

  alt OIDC scope present
    SSO-->>C: access_token + refresh_token + scope + id_token
  else OAuth-only scope
    SSO-->>C: access_token + refresh_token + scope
  end

  C->>SSO: GET /userinfo (Bearer access_token)
  alt scope has openid
    SSO-->>C: 200 { sub, email? }
  else no openid scope
    SSO-->>C: 403 insufficient_scope
  end

  C->>SSO: POST /token (grant_type=refresh_token, refresh_token, client creds)
  SSO->>R: Verify session + rotate refresh token
  SSO-->>C: new access_token + new refresh_token

  C->>SSO: POST /logout (Bearer access_token)
  SSO->>R: Remove session + device mapping + userSessions item
  SSO-->>C: logout success

  Note over C,SSO: OIDC metadata: /.well-known/openid-configuration<br/>JWKS: /.well-known/jwks.json (RS256)